The information was advanced mid-afternoon today by the Presidency of the Republic. "President Erdoğan has cancelled his visit to Guinea-Bissau and decided to return home. Erdogan will attend the NATO Leaders' Summit, which will be held online tomorrow," reads a note posted on the Presidency's Facebook page. On this tour of Africa, Recep Tayyip Erdoğan has visited the Democratic Republic of Congo and Senegal. In Bissau, as well as being decorated by his counterpart Umaro Sissoco Embaló, to whom the Turkish president was supposed to express his solidarity for the alleged coup attempt on February 1. The agenda of the visit also included the signing by the governments of Co-operation agreements in the fields of transport, media and defence. Turkey was one of the first countries visited by Embaló in 2020. --ChannelAfrica--